(h) The Iambic Senarius was used in Roman Comedy as the ordinary metre of Diverbia‚ i.e. narrative passages and spoken conversation or soliloquies of a quiet type (see Introd. 4)'. The action of the Menaechmi is so rapid that less than a third of it is written in this metre. Usually the proportion of Senarii is larger.
